                     <h2 class="title-blue">
                    Reporting Tools</h2>
                     <h2 class="title-blue">
                        Power BI
                    </h2>
                    <p>
                        Power BI is technology driven business intelligence tool used by Microsoft to analyse and visualize raw data to present actionable items. It combines business analytics, data visualization and best practices to help organizations make data-driven decisions. Power BI helps business users access data in user-friendly formats, such as dashboards, reports, and datasets. It is designed to help business users gain insights from their data like no other technology. Power BI is a hybrid of on-premises and cloud components. In order to view the reports it requires the end users to use only a web browser or tablets for native mobile applications.
                    </p>
                    <h2 class="title-blue">
                        Tableau</h2>
                    <br />
                    <p>
                        Tableau is Business Intelligence (BI) tool that can help you create beautiful and
                        visually-renders reports, charts, dashboardsand graphs using your data. These reports
                        are interactive and can easily be shared with anyone. This data visualization software
                        is extremely robust and easy to use that it has a drag and drop interface, so you
                        need not be a techie to use it.Tableau helps you visualize & analyze your big data
                        and it can be a great source in helping you solve your complex business problems.
                        Visual representation of data can be very helpful in finding solutions to a lot
                        of problem.
                    </p>
                    <h2 class="title-blue">
                        SQL</h2>
                    <p>
                        SQL (Structured Query Language) is an interactive programming language for getting
                        information from a database. It can also update information in a database. SQL is
                        both an ANSI and an ISO standard many database products support SQL with proprietary
                        extensions to the standard language. SQL Queries take the form of a command language
                        that lets you select, insert, update, find out the location of data, and so on.
                        SQL is the standard language for Relation Database Management System. All RDBMS
                        like Oracle, Sybase, Informix, postgres and MySQL, MS Access, SQL Server use SQL
                        as standard database language.
                    </p>
                    <h2 class="title-blue">
                        Jira
                    </h2>
                    <p>
                        JIRA is project management software developed by Australian company Atlassian. The software is based on agile methods. The tool handles versatile activities such as debugging, issue tracking and project management. Many companies also use Jira software in a non-standard way as a warehouse automation tool, Document flow, cost optimization, etc. Jira Includes Dashboard and various useful functions and features to deal with problems easily. Among the most popular agile project management solutions, JIRA recently has adapted several products for all types of teams and organizations, including IT, marketing, operations, finance, HR, legal and other departments.
                    </p>
                    <h2 class="title-blue">
                        Ms Visio
                    </h2>
                    <p>
                        Microsoft Visio is software for drawing various diagrams These include organizational charts, Flowcharts, architectural plans, floor plans, data flow diagrams, processes Diagrams, business process modelling, pool diagrams, 3D maps, etc. It is a Microsoft product sold in addition to MS Office Microsoft Visio can be used to create chart. It offers a wide variety of shapes, objects and built-in models to work together.
                    </p>
                    <h2 class="title-blue">
                        Balsamiq
                    </h2>
                    <p>
                        Balsamiq Mock-ups is a GUI Mock-up generator app. It allows designers to organize pre-made widgets by using a drag-and-drop WYSIWYG editor. Balsamiq is a great tool for all wireframing, collaboration requirements. Wireframes are about reaching consensus on the features to be developed and Balsamiq will finally ask the team to align with the feature in terms of layout. It also supports cross-team collaboration, so team members can collaborate with various co-located or remote teams.
                    </p>
                    <h2 class="title-blue">
                        Axure RP
                    </h2>
                    <p>
                        Axure RP is a powerful design tool that can create Interactive HTML prototypes for web, mobile and desktop app projects RP in Axure RP stands for Rapid Prototyping. It is a fully integrated application that provides different design tools that should be used to create these prototypes. With the help of the architecture and wireframes, designers can easily continue to translate Prototypes direct from Axure. When a designer entrusts a project to a developer, he can better understand how certain things should be implemented and how they work, estimate and evaluate, reach more effectively.
                    </p>
